column4: The date and time when the contact address was created.
The address configured for the contact.
The first name that is specified in the contact address.
The label specified for the contact address. The label is used to refer to the contact address on the interface.
The last name that is specified in the contact address.
The middle name that is specified in the contact address.
The name prefix specified in the contact address.
The name suffix specified in the contact address.
The organization that is specified in the contact address.
The contact who is the owner of the contact address. The contact address is displayed on the view page of this contact.
The postal code specified in the contact address.
Defines whether the contact address is a primary contact address.
The region specified in the contact address.
The first line of the street address. Usually contains the street name and the building number.
The second line of the street address. May contain the appartment number, P.O. box, building name, etc.
The address types (whether it is a billing address, shipping address, or both) configured for the contact address.
The date and time when the contact address was last updated.
OroCRM user who has created the record.
A collection of accounts where the contact is set as default.
Personal information of people with whom a user gets in touch during the business activities.
First name of the contact person.
The set of contacts classed together by some common factor. Contact groups are mainly used to simplify the configuration of filters and segments.
The name used to refer to the contact group on the interface.
Contact groups the contact belongs to.

Add and Replace strategy adds new contact information from the imported file and updates the existing one.
Add strategy does not change existing records. All contacts are added as new records allowing duplicates.
Job title of the contact person within their organization.
Last name of the contact person.
Preferred way of communication for this contact.
The mean of communications with the contact.
The label of the contact method ('Email,' 'Mail,' or ' Phone').
Middle name of the contact person.
Name prefix or honorific of the contact person (Mr./Ms., Dr., Prof., etc.)
Name suffix of the contact person (Sr./Jr., M.D., OBE, etc.)
Photo or other identifying image of the contact.
A contact who serves as direct supervisor of the contact within their organization.
How the information about the contact was recieved.
The label of the contact source ('Phone Call,' 'Other Source,' TV,' or 'Website').
OroCRM user who had last updated the record.
Contact reason has been saved successfully
Contact request has been saved successfully
